-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Aug 26
-- 
-- Tue Aug 26, 2014 03:04AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Aug 26 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Interior Ministry Chief Secretary Svetlozar Lazarov said Bulgaria could build a barbed-wire fence along the entire border with Turkey, adding that 2,700 illegal immigrants entered the country this year and another 10,800 were turned back (Monitor, Sega, Presa). -- The interim government should immediately launch a procedure for a new debt, Boiko Borisov, leader of the GERB party which is expected to win the early elections in October, said (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor).   -- Bulgarian Interim Deputy Prime Ekaterina Zaharieva will head the energy board that is expected to be established on Wednesday, according to a draft decree of the interim government (Trud, Standart, Sega, Monitor).